snippet.textDisplay:
these forecasts are useless because we have no idea the true infection rate in China.... inability to test + many people don't test/self-quarantine + many people never develop symptoms beyond mild so never report it. moreover, much of the spread was pre-quarantine pre-awareness. if you applied the Wuhan mortality rates to US, annualized per capita, it would be nearly half a million dead (flu is about 60K a year). but if you apply post-quarantine rates in Beijing, it would be much less severe than the flu. moreover, we have no idea the true mortality rate because we don't know how many reports go unreported .... TBH we won't truly know until COVID is in an entirely post-quarantine post-awareness sample with very proactive rates of testing -- e.g. Korea or Japan maybe.

Iran data I would imagine must be far far worse than they're reporting. not just 1 but 2 Canadians (two!) catch it while visiting Iran... and the Health Minister got it.... what are the chances those 3 people all know the same 20-30 cases (over 1-2 weeks ago when they caught it). improbable. there must be thousands of cases in Irans.
